The port was modified to expose a roster-only Reader API, integrate a bounded
in-process container decoder, retain bounded selective GVAS parsing, avoid all
network and save-tree write operations, read persisted player
transforms/date-times, enforce bounded input/output, and support the Palworld
July 2026 guild-role layout.

No Palworld save, account identifier, player name, or proprietary Oodle runtime
or source is included in this directory. The Mermaid-compatible decoder source
is under internal/palsav, is distributed under GPL-3.0-or-later, and is linked
into the same server executable. These files retain their Apache-2.0 terms and
attribution; the combined executable is distributed under GPL-3.0-or-later.
See the top-level LICENSING.md for component scope and unresolved upstream
provenance.
